records.addlTxt:
Defendant Jericka N Bernal in court with attorney Christopher J. Cherella.  Denis John Stingl appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Court finds State has complied with victim notification.  Sentencing hearing proceeded.  Statements made as to sentencing. 

The Court sentenced the defendant to a MAXIMUM TERM OF IMPRISONMENT of 4 YEARS, with credit for 6 days time served; the INITIAL TERM OF CONFINEMENT in the Wisconsin State Prison System is 2 YEARS; the MAXIMUM TERM OF EXTENDED SUPERVISION is 2 YEARS.  
The defendant IS eligible for the Challenge Incarceration Program and IS eligible for the "Wisconsin Substance Abuse Program". 

Court orders the following conditions of extended supervision:  
*No contact with victim Bryon W.;
*No contact with victim's wife, Juana W.;
*No contact with establishment where incident occurred;
*No weapons;
*Cooperate with agent;
*No new offenses;
*Absolute sobriety;
*Alcohol assessment and follow through with treatment recommendations. 

Based upon stipulation of the parties, Court orders restitution in the amount of $130.06 awarded to Byron W. 
Defendant shall provide a DNA sample for the Data Bank and pay all appropriate costs.
Court ordered defendant to pay all applicable court costs, surcharges and restitution.   
As to all costs, surcharges and restitution, Court orders DOC shall collect prison funds at an amount or percentage deemed appropriate by the Department of Corrections.  Remaining balance to be collected during the period of extended supervision.  Unpaid amount to convert to a civil judgment.  

Court advised defendant that as a convicted felon she may never possess a firearm, body armor or ammunition.  Court advised defendant that her voting rights are suspended and she may not vote in any election until his civil rights are restored. Court advised defendant of her right to seek post conviction relief.

**Case is recalled.  Court orders correction to sentence.  At the request of the State, Court orders that restitution in the amount of $130.06 awarded to CRIME VICTIM COMPENSATION FUND.  

Filed,
Written Explanation of Determinate Sentence;
Notice of Right to Seek Post Conviction Relief;
Ineligible Voting Notice & Acknowledgement;
Pretrial Incarceration Credit.
